sentence: Mars Williams (born May 29, 1955) is an American jazz and rock saxophonist.
Mars Williams (born May 29, 1955) is an American jazz and rock saxophonist.

Exposed to big band and dixieland jazz by his trumpet-playing father, Williams played classical clarinet for ten years, then migrated to saxophone in his last year of high school, citing the influence of Eric Dolphy, John Coltrane, and Charlie Parker.
